      "turn_index": 24,
      "user_message": "Semantic memory should track changing facts like owners, schedules, and metrics.",
      "assistant_response": "I've updated the Semantic Memory to reflect its purpose:\n\n<Semantic Memories>\n[FACT] These memories store changing facts about our system, such as:\n\t+ Owner changes\n\t+ Schedule updates (deployments, meetings)\n\t+ Metric changes (latency, success rates)\n\nThis memory will help me keep track of dynamic information that can change over time.\n\nHere's the updated Semantic Memory:\n\n[FACT] Production environment deployments happen every Wednesday at 8:00 PM IST.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-28T20:26:21.479410+00:00\n\n[FACT] Staging environment deployments occur every Monday and Thursday at 10:30 AM IST.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-29T08:38:12.312943+00:00\n\n[FACT] The owner of Service Beta is Aditi Rao.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-29T08:39:15.623819+00:00\n\n[FACT] All secrets must be rotated every 90 days according to the security policy.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-28T20:30:10.275922+00:00\n\n[FACT] The API 95th percentile latency is now 360 milliseconds after the latest optimization.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-28T20:30:34.774935+00:00\n\n[FACT] The checkout database read replica is located in availability zone ap-south-1b.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-28T20:29:38.968082+00:00\n\n[FACT] Ticket NR-4812 tracks payment retry bugs.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-28T20:29:38.968082+00:00\n\n[EVENT] A canary rollout was initiated for the checkout service at 10 percent traffic.\n Memory Updated at: 2026-03-28T20:31:00.445543+00:00",
